  "content": {
    "problemStatement": "For positive integer **x** let define function **F(x) = 1 * (1! + x) + 2 * (2! + x) + .. + x * (x! + x)**. \n\n**\"k!\"** means factorial: **k! = 1 * 2 * .. * k** \n\n\n\nChef wants to calculate **F(p1) + F(p2) + ... + F(pn)**. \n\nAs answer could be large, help him, calculate value modulo **m**.",
    "constraints": [
      "**1** ≤ **n** ≤ ** 105**",
      "**1** ≤ ****pi**** ≤ ** 1018**",
      "**1** ≤ **m** ≤ ** 107**",
      "Subtasks Subtask #1: **1** ≤ ****pi**** ≤ ** 6 ** (10 points)",
      "Subtask #2: **1** ≤ ****pi**** ≤ ** 7 * 103** (25 points)",
      "Subtask #3: **m** - prime number (25 points)",
      "Subtask #4: original constraints (40 points)"
    ],
    "inputFormat": "**n****m****n****pi**",
    "outputFormat": "**m**",
    "sampleTestCases": [
      {
        "id": "sample_1",
        "input": "5 7\n1 2 3 4 5",
        "output": "6",
        "explanation": "Explanation:\nF(1) = 1 * (1! + 1) = 2\nF(2) = 1 * (1! + 2) + 2 * (2! + 2) = 3 + 8 = 11\nF(3) = 1 * (1! + 3) + 2 * (2! + 3) + 3 * (3! + 3) = 4 + 10 + 27 = 41\nF(4) = 1 * (1! + 4) + 2 * (2! + 4) + 3 * (3! + 4) + 4 * (4! + 4) = 5 + 12 + 30 + 112 = 159\nF(5) = 1 * (1! + 5) + 2 * (2! + 5) + 3 * (3! + 5) + 4 * (4! + 5) + 5 * (5! + 5) = 794\nF(1) + F(2) + F(3) + F(4) + F(5) = 2 + 11 + 41 + 159 + 794 = 1007\n1007 modulo 7 = 6"
      }
    ]
  },
